    "updated_at": "2014-08-30T06:37:39Z",
    "body": "This may be a very untested part of the compiler (as it may have never been exercised before), so it would be nice to see a larger array of tests to ensure that this feature does indeed work. Some things such as:\n- If a `!` closure returns, an error should be generated.\n- Code after a `!` closure invocation should be dead.\n- Calling a `!` closure in a `!` function should be ok\n",
